新调查发现，超过一半的艺术家会隐藏在音乐中使用人工智能https://www.nme.com/news/music/over-half-of-artists-would-conceal-ai-use-in-their-music-new-survey-finds-3527917?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=超过一半的艺术家会在他们的音乐中隐藏人工智能的新调查发现Liberty DunworthWed, 01 Nov 2023 12:14:16 +0000 Music NewsNews https://www.nme.com/?p=3527917 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studi-home@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="家庭录音室照片" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studi-home@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studi-home@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studi-home@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studi-home@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studi-home@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studi-home@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>它还透露，大约四分之一的音乐家已经尝试过人工智能</p><p>新的调查发现<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/over-half-of-artists-would-conceal-ai-use-in-their-music-new-survey-finds-3527917">，超过一半的艺术家会在他们的音乐中隐瞒人工智能的使用，新的调查结果</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studi-home@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="家庭录音室照片" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studi-home@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studi-home@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studi-home@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studi-home@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studi-home@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studi-home@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>一项新的研究表明，超过一半的艺术家会选择不透露他们使用人工智能来帮助制作音乐。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/ai-music-oasis-liam-gallagher-drake-weeknd-3432529">在人工智能绿洲时代，平凡是没有意义的</a></strong></li></ul><p>此前，全球音乐工作室网络<a href="https://pirate.com/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Pirate</em></a>最近进行了一项调查，旨在探索新的人工智能技术对音乐行业的影响。</p><p>在这项研究中，来自英国、美国和德国的 1000 多名音乐家被问及他们对使用人工智能创作音乐的开放程度，以及他们使用这些平台辅助自己工作的潜力。</p><p> Overall, the study found that there was a growing acceptance of the concept, with 25 per cent of all those surveyed admitting to having already dabbled with the technologies in their own music production. Of the remaining three quarters who hadn&#39;t yet experimented with AI, 46 per cent said that they would be willing to try using the tools in the future.</p><p> More revealing, however, of the total number of people surveyed, only 48 per cent of artists confirmed that they would tell their listeners when AI was involved in their music, and 53 per cent admitted that they were concerned about how their audience would react if they knew the music they were listening to was aided by artificial intelligence. </p><figure id="attachment_3527922" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3527922" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3527922" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studio@2000x1270.jpg" alt="Home Recording Studio Stock Photo" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studio@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studio@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studio@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studio@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studio@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/studio@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3527922" class="wp-caption-text"> Home Recording Studio Stock Photo. CREDIT: mixetto/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> The report from <em>Pirate</em> also noted that 55 per cent of artists are actively acquiring new skills in response to ongoing advancements in AI. 28 per cent of which are learning skills directly related to AI, while 37 per cent are learning skills that don&#39;t directly correspond to the technologies.</p><p> Over recent months, the prospect of using AI platforms to create music has been one that has divided both emerging and established musicians, with some wholly opposed to the concept, while others have taken a more open-minded approach.</p><p> One of the most prominent artists to speak out against the method is <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nick-cave">Nick Cave</a> , who previously <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nick-cave-calls-chatgpt-and-ai-songwriting-a-grotesque-mockery-of-what-it-is-to-be-human-3381620">described the prospect as a “grotesque mockery of what it is to be human”</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nick-cave-chatgpt-should-just-fuck-off-and-leave-songwriting-alone-3421859">told platforms such as ChatGPT to “fuck off and leave songwriting alone”</a> .</p><p> Others who have criticised it include <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sting">Sting</a> , who said AI “doesn&#39;t impress” him, <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/stereophonics">Stereophonics</a> frontman <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/stereophonics-kelly-jones-hits-out-at-use-of-ai-in-songwriting-3473528">Kelly Jones, who said that art is about “a real person&#39;s expression”</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/guns-n-roses">Guns N&#39; Roses</a> bassist <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/duff-mckagan">Duff McKagan</a> , who said <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/duff-mckagan-not-worried-about-ai-in-music-its-not-gonna-affect-my-creativity-3511911">he&#39;s “not worried” about AI in music as it won&#39;t “affect my creativity”</a> .</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/grimes">Grimes</a> was more open to the concept, however, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-gives-fans-permission-to-use-her-voice-on-songs-created-by-ai-3434810">permitting fans to use her voice in their own AI projects</a> – provided they share the royalties with her. <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/liam-gallagher">Liam Gallagher</a> also seemed pretty impressed with the <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/heres-a-lost-oasis-album-created-by-ai-3432125">AI-made “Lost” Oasis album</a> earlier this year, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/liam-gallagher-responds-to-lost-oasis-album-made-by-ai-3432480">describing the finished product as “mega”</a> .</p><p> Following the technologies gathering such rapid momentum across the industry, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/uk-music-makers-share-five-fundamental-rules-for-industry-using-ai-3501881">the Council of Music Makers (CMM) developed five fundamental rules</a> that they want companies to embrace when it comes to developing AI platforms.</p><p> The guidelines were officially unveiled at the Ivors Academy Global Creators Summit on music and AI in London in September, and outlined that the rights of music-makers must be respected and profits must be shared fairly.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/over-half-of-artists-would-conceal-ai-use-in-their-music-new-survey-finds-3527917">More than half of artists would conceal use of AI in their music, new survey finds</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
